.TH "fcoe_ctlr_device_add" 9 "fcoe_ctlr_device_add" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fcoe_ctlr_device_add \- Add a FIP ctlr to sysfs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct fcoe_ctlr_device *" fcoe_ctlr_device_add
.BI "(struct device *parent "  ","
.BI "struct fcoe_sysfs_function_template *f "  ","
.BI "int priv_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "parent" 12
The parent device to which the fcoe_ctlr instance
should be attached
.IP "f" 12
The LLD's FCoE sysfs function template pointer
.IP "priv_size" 12
Size to be allocated with the fcoe_ctlr_device for the LLD
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine allocates a FIP ctlr object with some additional memory
for the LLD. The FIP ctlr is initialized, added to sysfs and then
attributes are added to it.
